                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20290B/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-12T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 12, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1406. From the Under Secretary. Colonel Harold B. Hoskins has been instructed to
                    proceed to Cairo to conduct a survey for the Joint Chiefs of Staff. The
                    Department and the President, with whom I have discussed the subject, are
                    interested in facilitating his mission and I shall appreciate your giving him
                    assistance and advice in accomplishing his purpose. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
